  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resources Generalist (Ref 13479)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Process monthly payroll related activities including calculation of gross and net pay, deductions, and other payroll-related adjustments, claims reimbursement</li><li>Ensure accurate and compliant payroll tax and statutory contributions</li><li>Liaise with employees to address payroll-related inquiries and resolve any discrepancies</li><li>Maintain and update employee payroll records and documentation</li><li>Assist with the preparation of payroll reports and analysis</li><li>Stay up-to-date with changes in payroll regulations and requirements</li><li>Interface with HR customers handling payroll queries</li><li>Support billing operations such as customer billing</li><li>Ensure billing timeliness and accuracy.</li><li>Manage onboarding and new hire and offboarding process (preparation of agreement, negotiations of benefits, involvement in work pass applications)</li><li>Work closely with customers to handle employee related issues which encompass counseling, grievances process, disciplinary and termination</li><li>Follow-up on staff renewal, performance, etc.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Human Resources / Business Administration / Accountancy with 1 to 2 years experience in payroll processing</li><li>Strong attention to detail and excellent numerical skills</li><li>Have good communication and presentation skills</li><li>Good knowledge of the Singapore Employment Act would be an added advantage.</li><li>Able to work independently on a broad variety of projects.</li><li>Have good professional appearance</li><li>Have a strong level of influence and negotiation skills</li></ul><p>License No : 12C6060</p>",
